        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 1 at 7:22PM MDT until August 1 at 7:45PM MDT by NWS Albuquerque NM</headline>
        <description>At 722 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line from
near Trujillo to near Montezuma, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect
wind damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Las Vegas, Romeroville, Storrie Lake State Park, Trujillo,
Tecolote, San Agustin, Los Montoyas and Ojitos Frios.

This includes the following highways...
State Road 518 between Mile Markers 1 and 6.
State Road 283 between Mile Markers 1 and 4.
Interstate 25 between Mile Markers 333 and 359.
State Road 65 between Mile Markers 1 and 4.
State Road 104 between Mile Markers 1 and 35.
</description>
        <instruction>Anyone outdoors should move to shelter inside a well-built structure
and stay away from windows. These storms are capable of producing
dangerous hail and damaging winds.

Accumulations of small hail on roads can create very slick and
hazardous driving conditions.

Motorists can expect brief but sudden changes in visibility and
ponding of water on roadways as storms move through the area.</instruction>
